            <title><![CDATA[Battlefield 6 Release Date Reportedly Leaks]]></title>
            <link>https://www.gamespot.com/articles/battlefield-6-release-date-reportedly-leaks/1100-6533386/?ftag=CAD-01-10abi2f</link>
            <guid>https://www.resetera.com/threads/battlefield-6-release-date-reportedly-leaks.1251501/</guid>
            <content:encoded><![CDATA[<div id="readability-page-1" class="page"><p>
    <span data-nosnippet="">GameSpot may receive revenue from affiliate and advertising partnerships for sharing this content and from purchases through links.</span>
  </p><article itemscope="" data-type-id="1100" data-guid="1100-6533386">

            
            
  


        

  


        
        
              <section>

                  
          <div data-content-element-selector="p, .js-buylink-item-container" data-allowed-classes-selector="js-buylink-item-container">
                <p><a href="https://www.gamespot.com/articles/battlefield-6-release-date-trailer-news/1100-6526583/" data-ref-id="1100-6526583">Battlefield 6</a> is set for its official unveiling on July 24, but a new report might have spoiled some of the surprise. A report from reputable leaker <a href="https://www.dealabs.com/magazine/battlefield-6-date-de-sortie-editions-prix-precommande-on-vous-devoile-toutes-nos-infos-inedites-60267" data-target="true" target="_blank" rel="noopener nofollow">Dealabs</a> claims Battlefield 6 will launch on October 10 for PS5, Xbox Series X|S, and PC.</p><p>An October release date for Battlefield 6 was <a href="https://www.gamespot.com/articles/battlefield-6-release-date-trailer-news/1100-6526583/" data-ref-id="1100-6526583">previously reported</a>, so it's not a total shock. The latest rumor is that Activision's <a href="https://x.com/TheGhostOfHope/status/1945861417485099010" data-target="true" target="_blank" rel="noopener nofollow">Call of Duty: Black Ops 7 will release on November 14</a>. If both dates are legitimate, that would put about a month of time between both releases.</p><p>It's been four years since there were new entries in the Call of Duty and Battlefield franchises releasing the same year, going back to 2021 with Call of Duty: Vanguard and Battlefield 2042.</p><p>Officially, EA has only confirmed that Battlefield 6 will be <a href="https://www.gamespot.com/articles/battlefield-6-will-be-fully-revealed-this-summer-launching-by-march-2026/1100-6531349/" data-ref-id="1100-6531349">released by the end of March 2026. </a></p><p>The Dealabs report also mentioned that Battlefield 6 will be available in Standard and Phantom editions, the latter of which is said to be digital-only and will include extra in-game content. The report also claimed that EA will not offer early access to the game, but it will instead debut on October 10 for everyone.</p><p>The standard edition is rumored to be priced at €80 ($94 USD) for PS5 and Xbox Series X|S and €70 ($82 USD) on PC, with the Phantom edition selling for €110.00 ($130 USD) on console and €100 ($117) on PC. The Dealabs report had no mention of pricing for Battlefield 6 in USD; the figures above are only conversions based on the European source. Finally, the report said preorders will open on July 31.</p><p>The first trailer for Battlefield 6 will be releases on July 24. A <a href="https://www.gamespot.com/articles/battlefield-6-teases-all-out-war-ahead-of-full-reveal/1100-6533382/" data-ref-id="1100-6533382">teaser video, however, is out now, and it teases all-out war.</a> An <a href="https://www.gamespot.com/articles/battlefield-6-open-beta-confirmed-will-include-this-key-change/1100-6533303/" data-ref-id="1100-6533303">open beta for Battlefield 6</a> is on the way, but a date for it has yet to be confirmed.</p><p>Battlefield Studios is heading up the development of Battlefield 6, with subsidiaries DICE, Criterion, Ripple Effect, and Motive Studio working on various aspects of the project.</p>
  
                        
    
        
        
  
